column2: Lake level high because of recent rains.
Water level way above normal- cloudy- and no wind.
Beautiful day- 78 degrees- and light breeze.
Partly cloudy- lake very high because of over 8" of rain this past week.  Totogatic River backs into lake- and some algae.  Lake level: very high
Nice sunny October day- some algae bloom in bays.
90 degrees- partly sunny- and cloud cover at time of test.
Hazy- 70 degrees- recent rains may have changed clarity of water.
Because of recent rains lake is very high.  Too dirty for swimming- 7/6 about 4 1/2'over normal.
Algae bloom on the lake- bright day- and windy.
Sunny- 72 degrees- humid- lake high and full of sediment because of recent rains.
Sunny- 82 degrees- pine pollen on lake- and the lake is not good for swimming.
Beautiful day- 65 degrees- and very little bloom noted on the lake.
Heavy 4" rain night before and sunny.
Sunny- 70 degrees- after a week of 50 degree weather.
Algae starting to come- cloudy day- and cool.
A lot of swimmers itch on the lake.
Water in lake rose 6' after backup of water from Totogactic River and 11 1/2" rain.
Ice off- no bloom- slight chop- clear day.
Water 75 degrees- light chop- some algal bloom started.
Rain 8/7- windy- slight sign of algal.
Windy-has algal boom-also river had backed up.  Water level was high (2') but receding
Water temp. 40 degrees- sunny with med. breeze.  Level high due to river backup.
Ice off April 29th. Lake rose 6'. Now normal.  Lake level: Rising
Some pollen on surface. Water level: Up some about 10"
Partly cloudy- slight breeze.  Water level: Up about 1'
Lake up 6' due to river back up.  Water level: Very high
Storm night before lots of wind.
Heavy wind night before and rain.
Water temp. 57 degrees- clear but windy 25 mph. Light algae bloom.
Bright day- water temp. 52 degrees- heavy algae bloom- wind calm.
Ice out 4/21/97- lake rose 6" but now normal.
Water temp. 51 degrees. Slight chop- wind from N.
Temp 70 degrees. Slight chop from E. Water level: up 2" due to beaver dam
Slight chop temp. 66 degrees. Surface covered with pine pollen.
Slight chop- water temp. 70 degrees. Never seen as nice as this year but cooler than average.
Water temp. 75 degrees. Algae starting to grow.
Sunny day- slight bloom- water temp. 70 degrees.
Water temperature 65 degrees.  Windy and clear.
Windy.  Temperature 54 degrees.  Had 4 inches of rain in the last 2 weeks.  Water level: up six inches.
Lots of traffic.  Some algae starting.
Fairly calm- partly cloudy- traffic low.  Lake is great.
South breeze.  Algae highest of year.  Weeds are dying.  Surface temp 64 F.
Light breeze- weeds dying- temp 55 F surface temp.
Calm- weeds rotting- surface temp 52 F.
Ice out 4/18/2002. Windy- partly sunny- surface temperature=70 degrees F.
Lots of boat traffic- windy- sunny- surface temperature is 80 degrees F.
Light breeze- sunny- surface temperature is 74 degrees F- Slight algae.
Light breeze- sunny- surface temperature is 68 degrees F.
Slight breeze- partly cloudy- surface temperature is 70 degrees F- not much algae.
Calm- sunny- surface temperature is 60 degrees F- algae is at its highest point.
Windy- sunny- surface temperature is 52 degrees F. Algae and murky.
Algae breaking up.  Weeds growing.  Water 78F
Heavy wind day before- water 78 F
Water 52 F.  Lake starting to turn over.  Some weeds still blooming.
Water 53 F- windy.  Water high.  Beaver dam in outlet.
Light Wind- Beaver Dam Out- Surface Temp. 75 degrees
light wind- some algae- partly sunny
sunny- light wind- water temp 68 degrees
I was unable to enter the d.o.5'd.o 8  10'd.o.7 15'd.o.7 20'd.o.3 25'd.o.1 30.do.0
the pine and popple pollen was very thick- because of heavy rain the river pushed into the lake raised it abut two feet leaving alot of brown sediment in the lake
the weather was very nice for the three day weekend lthe lake was very busy.

sunshine 80 degrees Lake is about 1.5 feet high because of a beaver dam in the creek  flowing into the river. It should be removed so the lake could drain properly. Tere are six loons on the lake this year.

We had 2.225 in. of rain yesterday- sun shine and it is  76 degrees today the beaver dam was taken out early this month- but has been rebuilt the lake is cumming up again. the lake is quiet this week.
sun shine + little wind - there were only three fishing boats on the lake- the beavers keep rebiulding the dam in the in the creek the lake is about one foot high
A great day- 78 degrees few puffy clouds- with a slite breeze. A lot of pine + popple pollen on the lake and more comming. there were to loons in our bay when we stated out.
slightly overcast eighty degrees. lake level was normal bever dam has been opened up. one loon spotted on the lake. five fishing boats on the lake. No water skiers or personal watercraft.

The lake level came up two and a half feet early this month- the rain caused the river to push into the lake-it has went down but was about 10 inches high ai this time. The sun was shining slight breeze from the north- the lake water was very brown-
lake is a little high- one loon spotted- sunshine and very little wind.
overcast- temperture 56 degrees there was two boats fishing- lake level is up about six in. blue gill spawning has slowed down.

Weather was nice 72 degrees- slitly overcast very slite  breeze- very little boat traffic one fishing two water sking. lake level is normal lake has been high for about a month caused by rain raising the river and pushing into the lake. the water was not as clear as normal. No sighn of any wildlife today no loons.
Sunshine temp 64 degrees slight wind from the n.w lake level about normal.two fishing boats- didn't see any ducks- geese or loons today.

weather was sunny 71 degrees wind was out of the north the river flow has slowed. so the lake level was back to normal. The bluegils are starting to move into the shallows- for spawning there were five boats fishing. seen one loom. one familey of ducks.
the wind was out the northwest sunshine- we had 1.2 inches of rain yesterday

column1: there were two boats out on the lake. John Ney volunteerd to help with the moniteering.there were two loons on the lake as we were going out. the lake level was normal .

column2: Temperture was 88 degrees overcast sky four boats on the lake one pontoon three fishing spoted one eagle- and five geese.

weather was cool 51 degrees sunshine north wind. the ice went out may 8th the lake level went down to normal- now with the rain we had last weekend it has come up- it is three feet high now and may come little higher. there were two geese on the lake one eagle circling overhead no boats out

weather partly cloudy 68 degrees. The lake has returned to its normal level the water has cleared up but still has a brown color. There were three loons one fishing and one boat pulling tube. Jan Huse help with the monitering

whether nice sun shine- slight wind from the north. No wild life activity- no loons on the lake. one fishing boat- and a few people swimming and wading around the shore and docks. the water is clean very little algae.

The lake level is reseeding- we have gone from 4ft. high down to 1ft. high. the weather is clear very little south wind- 79 degrees- very few docks in people are waiting for the level to stay normal- one fishing boat out. I seen two geese- I didn't see any loons. John Ney helped.
the lake association purchased a DO meter so we will be reporting D.O.

column1: The weather was sunny slight breeze out of the south
the lake was calm their was one fishing boat- and two kayaks  also two loons on the lake
John Ney helped with the sampling.

column2: weather overcast sky 70 degrees no wind lake was calm there was one boat out and some people swimming + wading near there dock- there were three loons on the lake. John Ney helped we didn't record the oxygen this week

The lake is five feet high due to the recent rains we had- and that makes Totagatic river push into the lake. There are docks under water and floating- the water is a much darker brown with a lot of sediment in it.
Ice went out 3/30/15 lake had a lot of suspended dead vegetation

column1: there were two loons on the lake no other boats out yet the weather sunny and cold

column2: Sunshine 64 degrees no other boats on the lake a pair of mallard ducks

column1: only 5 piers in the lake the water has cleared up a lot sense last secchi data

column2: weather clear the lake was calm- no wind there were two boats out fishing. John Ney helped with the sampling- we

column1: did D.O this time the lake association purchased our own unit to do this. John Ney helped with the sampling this time the lake association purchased D.O meter so now we can do oxygen . the weather very nice sunshine no wind  the lake was calm- there were two fishing boats on the lake- there were two loons on the lake-

column2: The weather was sunshine 70 degrees and calm- very little activity on the lake there were three loons on the lake

column1: John Ney did the D O and temperature testing

column2: overcast sky slight wind temperature was cool 60 degrees- no boats using the lake one loon on the lake.

column1: the lake was high do to the five inches of rain earlier in the week

column2: 73 degrees sunshine south wind- there was no waterfowl on the lake two pontoons and one fishing boat very little activity around the lake.
sky was slight overcast- warm 72 degrees one fishing boat on the lake no wildlife seen very quiet slight breeze.
sunshine 50 degrees slight north wind- no shine of any wildlife- one other boat fishing
The sun was shinning with a slight breeze- there were two mallard drakes together one single loon on the lake no other boats on the lake about half of the piers in-
slight overcast calm the lake was very quiet one boat out fishing- the bluegill spawning has slowed down. There  is a lot of tree pollen floating in the water-  There were two loons on the lake-

The weather very nice very slight west breeze sun shine. I had two helpers today- Daryl Iverson and John Ney- they will help the rest of the year with plans replacing me next year. The bluegill spawning is about done there were four boats fishing- saw to eagles hear two loons.

I was unable to do testing in July do to the flooding of our lake. The lake was eleven feet above normal level this was the results of 12 inches of rain and A dam going out upstream on the river. We are down almost to normal now- the lake is very dark a lot brown sediment floating in the water. There were two boats out fishing two adult loons and to young. The weather was hot 90' south west wind.

sun slight breeze- two kayaks and one fishing boat on the lake- three loons two adults one baby The lake level is back to normal- there is a lot sediment suspended in the water. Daryl Iverson help with sampling he will be replacing me next year
